modules.description: This module supports operations to construct and format structured documents into readable ASCII text, using layout combinators like indentation, grouping, and spacing to control visual hierarchy. It manipulates abstract document trees (`doc`) and character streams (`t`), enabling precise control over line breaks, indentation, and width-constrained rendering. Typical applications include code formatters, configuration file generators, or structured log viewers where human-readable text layout with dynamic wrapping and alignment is required.

Constructs and formats structured documents into readable ASCII text using layout combinators for indentation, grouping, and spacing. It operates on abstract document trees and character streams, enabling precise control over line breaks, indentation, and width-constrained rendering. Used for code formatters, configuration file generators, and structured log viewers with dynamic wrapping and alignment.
